1
00:01:13,680 --> 00:01:14,480
Get down.

2
00:01:40,239 --> 00:01:41,000
Don't move.

3
00:01:44,040 --> 00:01:45,040
We'll meet again.

4
00:02:36,439 --> 00:02:37,439
Didn't you

5
00:02:37,919 --> 00:02:40,520
go to Hong Kong, China decades ago?

6
00:02:46,960 --> 00:02:47,840
An acquaintance?

7
00:02:51,879 --> 00:02:52,719
My Martial Uncle.

8
00:02:53,680 --> 00:02:55,199
Doesn't that make him my Martial Uncle too?

9
00:03:03,240 --> 00:03:04,759
Old Chen, are you sure?

10
00:03:04,960 --> 00:03:06,879
Claiming relatives is no small matter.

11
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:08,520
Ever since Zhang Daozhi was born,

12
00:03:08,520 --> 00:03:10,080
he's had an ingot-shaped birthmark.

13
00:03:10,080 --> 00:03:11,439
He's an old acquaintance of my grandfather.

14
00:03:11,479 --> 00:03:12,919
He specializes in I Ching Studies.

15
00:03:12,919 --> 00:03:14,719
Later, he became an antique appraisal expert,

16
00:03:14,759 --> 00:03:16,159
and started an antique business.

17
00:03:16,280 --> 00:03:17,719
In terms of seniority,

18
00:03:18,319 --> 00:03:19,719
I should call him Martial Uncle.

19
00:03:20,120 --> 00:03:21,159
I've also heard

20
00:03:21,639 --> 00:03:23,479
he's practiced Internal Martial Arts since childhood.

21
00:03:23,719 --> 00:03:24,520
His skills are profound.

22
00:03:24,759 --> 00:03:27,000
No one knows exactly how capable he is.

23
00:03:28,439 --> 00:03:30,400
I think this is a good thing, right?

24
00:03:30,479 --> 00:03:33,120
Having such a tough guy on our side,

25
00:03:33,280 --> 00:03:35,400
our team just got stronger!

26
00:03:35,919 --> 00:03:37,719
W-What do you mean stronger?

27
00:03:38,240 --> 00:03:39,599
What do you mean on our side?

28
00:03:40,080 --> 00:03:40,919
He's still suspicious.

29
00:03:45,199 --> 00:03:46,719
When we were at the Tomb-Quelling Stele,

30
00:03:46,840 --> 00:03:47,919
he already crossed paths with us.

31
00:03:47,919 --> 00:03:48,639
Right?

32
00:03:48,639 --> 00:03:50,240
Why didn't he show himself then?

33
00:03:56,199 --> 00:03:57,520
Tell me, why is this old man

34
00:03:57,520 --> 00:03:59,000
sneaking around following us?

35
00:04:00,240 --> 00:04:02,120
What is he really after?

36
00:04:02,120 --> 00:04:03,280
The Lingxiao Pearl.

37
00:04:06,879 --> 00:04:08,000
No, no, y-y-you...

38
00:04:08,000 --> 00:04:09,280
Go, go, go over there.

39
00:04:09,479 --> 00:04:10,080
Okay.

40
00:04:14,719 --> 00:04:17,040
Worthy nephew, has your fever broken?

41
00:04:26,079 --> 00:04:28,480
You brought the medical kit back.

42
00:04:28,720 --> 00:04:30,879
And you set that forest fire right on time.

43
00:04:31,199 --> 00:04:32,160
It's smoking.

44
00:04:36,040 --> 00:04:37,680
You set the fire too.

45
00:04:37,959 --> 00:04:39,560
I didn't expect these old bones of mine

46
00:04:39,560 --> 00:04:41,160
could actually be of help to you.

47
00:04:49,040 --> 00:04:51,040
Since you intended to help us,

48
00:04:51,560 --> 00:04:52,879
why didn't you show yourself?

49
00:04:53,560 --> 00:04:54,360
If you had just explained things,

50
00:04:54,360 --> 00:04:55,959
we could have traveled together.

51
00:04:56,079 --> 00:04:57,360
I know who you are,

52
00:04:57,360 --> 00:04:59,560
but do you know who I am?

53
00:05:00,480 --> 00:05:02,480
I dressed up like that

54
00:05:02,480 --> 00:05:03,160
originally hoping to use

55
00:05:03,160 --> 00:05:05,279
the mountain people's worship of masked spirits

56
00:05:05,279 --> 00:05:06,560
to deal with them.

57
00:05:07,279 --> 00:05:08,480
But I never expected

58
00:05:08,639 --> 00:05:09,759
that as soon as I showed my face,

59
00:05:09,759 --> 00:05:11,000
look how scared these two got.

60
00:05:11,399 --> 00:05:12,000
I...

61
00:05:12,639 --> 00:05:15,120
Th-th-they weren't scared at all.

62
00:05:15,399 --> 00:05:16,560
It was mostly me who got scared.

63
00:05:16,600 --> 00:05:17,720
Anyway, no matter what,

64
00:05:17,800 --> 00:05:19,319
we still have to thank you for saving us, Martial Uncle.

65
00:05:19,399 --> 00:05:20,720
If it weren't for your secret help,

66
00:05:20,720 --> 00:05:22,120
we probably wouldn't have made it this far.

67
00:05:22,120 --> 00:05:23,040
Don't mention it.

68
00:05:23,639 --> 00:05:24,439
Actually,

69
00:05:25,120 --> 00:05:26,959
I had a bit of a selfish motive too.

70
00:05:27,279 --> 00:05:28,720
Relying solely on my own strength,

71
00:05:28,720 --> 00:05:30,879
I definitely wouldn't be able to see the Lingxiao Pearl.

72
00:05:31,160 --> 00:05:32,360
In fact, helping you

73
00:05:32,480 --> 00:05:33,759
is helping myself.

74
00:05:34,120 --> 00:05:35,560
At your advanced age,

75
00:05:35,560 --> 00:05:37,639
trekking over mountains and rivers for a pearl,

76
00:05:37,920 --> 00:05:38,680
is it really worth it?

77
00:05:39,839 --> 00:05:40,879
Logically speaking,

78
00:05:41,680 --> 00:05:42,879
it really isn't.

79
00:05:43,000 --> 00:05:44,519
But I heard that the Lingxiao Pearl

80
00:05:44,519 --> 00:05:47,439
hides a secret of the universe.

81
00:05:47,680 --> 00:05:48,680
So I just wanted

82
00:05:49,040 --> 00:05:50,519
in my lifetime

83
00:05:50,680 --> 00:05:52,319
to see its glory.

84
00:05:52,480 --> 00:05:53,680
Martial Uncle, but...

85
00:05:53,680 --> 00:05:55,120
I know what you want to say.

86
00:05:55,360 --> 00:05:58,519
I came this time just to take a look.

87
00:05:58,519 --> 00:06:00,240
As for after you find it,

88
00:06:01,079 --> 00:06:02,079
whether you give it to the state,

89
00:06:02,439 --> 00:06:04,639
take it away, or study it,

90
00:06:05,000 --> 00:06:06,600
I won't say a word against it.

91
00:06:08,480 --> 00:06:09,120
How about this?

92
00:06:09,120 --> 00:06:11,000
Martial Uncle has made his stance clear, right?

93
00:06:11,199 --> 00:06:12,680
Just to take a look.

94
00:06:13,120 --> 00:06:14,279
Take a look.

95
00:06:14,800 --> 00:06:16,000
Even if it costs me my life,

96
00:06:16,120 --> 00:06:17,360
it'll be totally worth it.

97
00:06:17,800 --> 00:06:18,360
Martial Uncle,

98
00:06:18,360 --> 00:06:19,600
then for the rest of the journey,

99
00:06:19,600 --> 00:06:20,759
we'll have to trouble you to look after us.

100
00:06:21,120 --> 00:06:22,120
Don't mention it.

101
00:06:22,920 --> 00:06:25,759
I don't think there's much left to look after.

102
00:06:25,759 --> 00:06:27,959
We've searched everywhere here, right?

103
00:06:28,040 --> 00:06:29,720
And we haven't seen the Lingxiao Pearl.

104
00:06:29,839 --> 00:06:31,879
This isn't the real Dian King's Tomb.

105
00:06:32,360 --> 00:06:33,360
The way I see it,

106
00:06:33,360 --> 00:06:35,360
there must be a hidden passage here.

107
00:06:35,360 --> 00:06:37,079
And the entrance to this passage is right...

108
00:06:39,759 --> 00:06:40,920
R-Right where?

109
00:06:42,680 --> 00:06:43,959
Right here.

110
00:06:46,959 --> 00:06:48,360
What are you standing around for?

111
00:06:48,759 --> 00:06:49,720
Push!

112
00:07:07,040 --> 00:07:08,160
There really is an opening!

113
00:07:08,560 --> 00:07:11,120
Martial Uncle, you're truly amazing.

114
00:07:11,560 --> 00:07:13,959
This chest is situated in the center, slightly north,

115
00:07:14,360 --> 00:07:16,160
but it has no feng shui significance.

116
00:07:16,439 --> 00:07:17,319
As the saying goes,

117
00:07:17,319 --> 00:07:19,560
things out of the ordinary must be suspicious.

118
00:07:20,480 --> 00:07:22,759
This is just a little bit of experience

119
00:07:23,319 --> 00:07:25,240
I've gathered over my years in the jianghu.

120
00:07:26,879 --> 00:07:28,079
After you, Martial Uncle.

121
00:07:40,759 --> 00:07:41,480
Martial Uncle

122
00:07:41,839 --> 00:07:44,639
You mentioned losing your men earlier.

123
00:07:45,319 --> 00:07:46,360
I brought twenty

124
00:07:46,360 --> 00:07:48,040
highly skilled brothers.

125
00:07:49,959 --> 00:07:50,879
With so many men,

126
00:07:50,879 --> 00:07:51,800
you still couldn't beat them?

127
00:07:52,000 --> 00:07:53,040
Don't even mention it.

128
00:07:53,360 --> 00:07:55,879
Do you think they're just ordinary mountain folk?

129
00:07:56,480 --> 00:07:58,240
Every one of them has a mission.

130
00:07:58,480 --> 00:08:00,360
They are the guardians of the Dian King's Tomb.

131
00:08:02,879 --> 00:08:05,480
Anyway, we've already made it this far.

132
00:08:05,839 --> 00:08:08,040
If you ask me, when we run into them later,

133
00:08:08,040 --> 00:08:08,959
we should just go around them.

134
00:08:09,160 --> 00:08:09,720
Hide from them.

135
00:08:09,720 --> 00:08:10,800
Just don't provoke them.

136
00:08:12,720 --> 00:08:13,360
What's wrong?

137
00:08:13,480 --> 00:08:14,759
My foot is stuck.

138
00:08:15,839 --> 00:08:16,639
Help me pull it out.

139
00:08:22,120 --> 00:08:23,839
What the hell is this junk?

140
00:08:27,639 --> 00:08:30,560
Underneath here are all... white bones!

141
00:08:32,279 --> 00:08:33,360
There are some under your feet too.

142
00:08:34,159 --> 00:08:35,279
Oh my god.

143
00:08:42,559 --> 00:08:43,360
What's that sound?

144
00:08:44,240 --> 00:08:44,879
Listen.

145
00:09:27,759 --> 00:09:28,559
What is that?

146
00:09:29,759 --> 00:09:30,960
These are vampire bats.

147
00:09:31,480 --> 00:09:32,639
Not only do they suck blood,

148
00:09:32,759 --> 00:09:34,159
they also spread the rabies virus.

149
00:09:36,960 --> 00:09:37,679
Old Lu!

150
00:09:38,759 --> 00:09:39,440
Fatty!

151
00:09:39,440 --> 00:09:40,159
Watch out!

152
00:09:40,879 --> 00:09:41,679
There are some here too!

153
00:09:43,639 --> 00:09:44,840
There are more and more of them!

154
00:09:49,200 --> 00:09:49,879
There are too many!

155
00:09:50,320 --> 00:09:51,200
We can't stay here.

156
00:09:51,679 --> 00:09:52,480
Move inside!

157
00:09:53,759 --> 00:09:54,399
Hurry!

158
00:09:57,279 --> 00:09:58,000
Watch out!

159
00:10:00,279 --> 00:10:00,919
Commander Chen!

160
00:10:01,159 --> 00:10:02,279
How about you take the others and go first?

161
00:10:02,279 --> 00:10:02,919
I've got plenty of meat.

162
00:10:02,919 --> 00:10:03,840
I'll hold them off here for a bit.

163
00:10:03,840 --> 00:10:04,840
Let them eat for a while.

164
00:10:05,080 --> 00:10:06,519
What's the point of them eating you?

165
00:10:06,519 --> 00:10:07,360
They are flying,

166
00:10:07,360 --> 00:10:08,440
and we are on foot.

167
00:10:08,720 --> 00:10:09,559
You won't get very far

168
00:10:09,559 --> 00:10:11,120
before we're all wiped out.

169
00:10:11,519 --> 00:10:12,159
Think of something!

170
00:10:14,960 --> 00:10:16,360
Think of something!

171
00:10:19,080 --> 00:10:19,919
Watch out!

172
00:10:36,919 --> 00:10:38,320
My body is steadfast.

173
00:10:38,879 --> 00:10:40,679
The way of Heaven, Earth, Man, and Ghost.

174
00:10:40,679 --> 00:10:41,879
I remain unharmed.

175
00:10:41,879 --> 00:10:43,360
I walk the true path.

176
00:10:43,960 --> 00:10:45,240
Enduring for ten thousand years.

177
00:10:45,320 --> 00:10:46,440
Untouched by gods and demons.

178
00:10:46,519 --> 00:10:48,039
United with the Dao.

179
00:10:48,320 --> 00:10:49,399
Evil spirits, disperse!

180
00:11:07,960 --> 00:11:08,759
Martial Uncle

181
00:11:09,279 --> 00:11:10,480
What kind of move is that?

182
00:11:10,679 --> 00:11:11,840
Can you teach me?

183
00:11:12,080 --> 00:11:13,360
It's just a minor trick.

184
00:11:13,360 --> 00:11:14,440
Nothing worth mentioning.

185
00:11:15,120 --> 00:11:16,240
The flame was green,

186
00:11:16,559 --> 00:11:17,559
and it emitted white smoke.

187
00:11:17,759 --> 00:11:19,559
Did you put phosphorus on that talisman?

188
00:11:20,039 --> 00:11:22,080
You rubbed it to heat the phosphorus

189
00:11:22,080 --> 00:11:23,279
to reach its ignition point.

190
00:11:23,440 --> 00:11:25,159
This young man is not bad.

191
00:11:25,159 --> 00:11:26,240
Smart.

192
00:11:26,759 --> 00:11:28,759
These bats have echolocation in their noses.

193
00:11:28,759 --> 00:11:31,360
They get confused when they hit the smoke.

194
00:11:31,559 --> 00:11:32,360
Impressive.

195
00:11:32,639 --> 00:11:33,919
I didn't expect your moves

196
00:11:33,919 --> 00:11:34,519
could actually be explained

197
00:11:34,519 --> 00:11:36,360
using modern science.

198
00:11:37,559 --> 00:11:38,360
Then, Martial Uncle,

199
00:11:38,519 --> 00:11:40,360
the incantation you just chanted

200
00:11:40,960 --> 00:11:43,559
has nothing to do with exorcism?

201
00:11:45,159 --> 00:11:47,440
When an expert performs magic in front of outsiders,

202
00:11:48,159 --> 00:11:49,960
there has to be some sense of ritual.

203
00:11:56,480 --> 00:11:57,960
That's... that's pretty impressive.

204
00:11:58,039 --> 00:11:58,799
This... this...

205
00:12:08,240 --> 00:12:09,080
What are you looking at?

206
00:12:09,720 --> 00:12:11,360
Look at this mural. Let me see.

207
00:12:16,919 --> 00:12:17,480
Isn't this...

208
00:12:17,480 --> 00:12:19,279
Isn't this the Lingxiao Pearl?

209
00:12:28,759 --> 00:12:29,480
Look, guys.

210
00:12:30,879 --> 00:12:32,360
Is this a sacrifice?

211
00:12:34,000 --> 00:12:35,919
This painting is too abstract.

212
00:12:36,759 --> 00:12:37,879
The people are flying into the sky.

213
00:12:38,879 --> 00:12:40,759
Maybe it's not about the painting style.

214
00:12:41,519 --> 00:12:42,519
Is it possible

215
00:12:42,759 --> 00:12:44,279
that there really is some force

216
00:12:44,639 --> 00:12:46,720
pulling people up into the sky?

217
00:12:47,039 --> 00:12:48,679
What kind of force could that be?

218
00:12:50,080 --> 00:12:52,360
A tornado blowing them all up?

219
00:12:52,360 --> 00:12:53,080
Look here.

220
00:12:53,360 --> 00:12:54,279
There are words here too.

221
00:12:55,360 --> 00:12:56,679
What on earth does this say?

222
00:12:59,159 --> 00:13:02,120
Early Tianhan era, year 29,

223
00:13:02,120 --> 00:13:03,159
year 64,

224
00:13:03,879 --> 00:13:05,440
year 180.

225
00:13:06,080 --> 00:13:07,360
Let me calculate this.

226
00:13:08,360 --> 00:13:12,320
This should be 104 BC,

227
00:13:12,960 --> 00:13:15,440
75 BC, 40 BC.

228
00:13:16,679 --> 00:13:17,879
My brain...

229
00:13:18,000 --> 00:13:19,360
Why didn't I become an accountant?

230
00:13:19,360 --> 00:13:20,799
Okay, okay.

231
00:13:21,159 --> 00:13:23,000
What a mess these years are.

232
00:13:23,559 --> 00:13:25,679
Since it's carved next to the sacrifice,

233
00:13:26,240 --> 00:13:27,759
it should be a record of

234
00:13:27,759 --> 00:13:29,679
the years the rituals were held.

235
00:13:29,679 --> 00:13:30,360
Right.

236
00:13:30,440 --> 00:13:32,639
Carved once for each sacrifice.

237
00:13:32,960 --> 00:13:36,080
From the first year of Tianhan to year 180,

238
00:13:36,440 --> 00:13:37,679
such a long time span,

239
00:13:38,320 --> 00:13:40,080
the Dian King couldn't have lived that long.

240
00:13:40,759 --> 00:13:42,360
Unless after his death,

241
00:13:42,639 --> 00:13:43,679
his descendants

242
00:13:43,960 --> 00:13:46,320
continued to hold the sacrificial rituals.

243
00:13:46,919 --> 00:13:49,080
Unless the prerequisite for immortality

244
00:13:49,639 --> 00:13:51,240
doesn't require the person to be alive.

245
00:13:52,159 --> 00:13:52,720
Fatty,

246
00:13:52,960 --> 00:13:54,519
you might have hit the nail on the head.

247
00:13:55,000 --> 00:13:56,159
What... what did I say?

248
00:13:56,720 --> 00:13:57,639
A tornado.

249
00:13:57,960 --> 00:13:58,639
The Dian King's sacrifice

250
00:13:58,639 --> 00:14:00,960
was likely waiting for a special celestial event.

251
00:14:02,080 --> 00:14:04,039
Commander Chen, do you remember?

252
00:14:04,320 --> 00:14:07,360
Didn't Yunling also have to wait for the blood moon?

253
00:14:07,360 --> 00:14:08,480
There are two types of celestial events.

254
00:14:08,720 --> 00:14:10,600
One refers to astronomical phenomena,

255
00:14:10,759 --> 00:14:13,039
the movement of the sun, moon, and stars.

256
00:14:13,360 --> 00:14:14,399
The other type

257
00:14:14,759 --> 00:14:16,840
is special meteorological changes.

258
00:14:18,559 --> 00:14:20,559
I think the Dian King was waiting for the latter.

259
00:14:20,840 --> 00:14:21,639
Celestial event...

260
00:14:22,480 --> 00:14:24,720
Didn't we just encounter a weather change?

261
00:14:27,320 --> 00:14:28,480
We're pretty lucky.

262
00:14:28,919 --> 00:14:29,679
Most likely,

263
00:14:29,759 --> 00:14:32,559
it's time for us to witness a miracle again.

264
00:14:32,559 --> 00:14:33,279
Come look quickly!

265
00:14:36,360 --> 00:14:37,320
Blister beetles.

266
00:14:37,960 --> 00:14:39,159
The inside of this bamboo pole,

267
00:14:39,159 --> 00:14:40,639
since it's been treated for anti-corrosion,

268
00:14:41,240 --> 00:14:42,159
logically speaking,

269
00:14:42,159 --> 00:14:44,279
shouldn't have the conditions for blister beetles to survive.

270
00:14:45,159 --> 00:14:46,759
How could they appear here?

271
00:15:04,120 --> 00:15:05,519
What did I tell you?

272
00:15:05,639 --> 00:15:06,320
No, no.

273
00:15:06,320 --> 00:15:07,519
Then let's start a fire, quick.

274
00:15:07,799 --> 00:15:09,360
No, we can't use fire.

275
00:15:09,440 --> 00:15:10,159
Bamboo is highly flammable.

276
00:15:10,159 --> 00:15:11,559
If you light a fire, we'll all die together!

277
00:15:11,559 --> 00:15:13,039
There are too many. We couldn't burn them all anyway.

278
00:15:13,159 --> 00:15:14,799
Martial Uncle, say something!

279
00:15:14,799 --> 00:15:15,519
What should we do?

280
00:15:15,919 --> 00:15:16,759
In my experience...

281
00:15:16,759 --> 00:15:19,039
At times like this, there's only one solution.

282
00:15:20,440 --> 00:15:21,159
What?

283
00:15:23,840 --> 00:15:24,480
Run!

